100 g Bacon Strips
4 unit(s) Flatbread
1.5 cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
½ cup Marinara Sauce
30 g Mixed Olives
1 unit(s) Diced Pineapple Cup
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 unit(s) Jalapeño
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
On a parchment-lined baking sheet, arrange bacon in a single layer.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 10-14 min, until bacon is crisp and cooked through.** Transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to cool.

Meanwhile, drain, then pat the pineapple dry with paper towels.
Drain, then thinly slice olives.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch strips.
Core, then thinly slice jalapeño into 1/4-inch rounds, removing seeds for less heat. (TIP: We suggest using gloves when prepping jalapeños!)

Thinly slice cooked bacon.
On an unlined baking sheet, arrange flatbreads. (NOTE: Cook two flatbreads per baking sheet.)
Top flatbreads with marinara sauce or BBQ sauce.
Place toppings in small serving bowls and allow each person to top their own flatbread.

Bake flatbreads in the middle of the oven for 7-8 min, until cheese is melted and flatbreads are crisp. (NOTE: For 4 servings, bake flatbreads in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.) (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)

Cut flatbreads into quarters.
Serve any remaining marinara sauce or BBQ sauce on the side for dipping.